<number box="[1246,1276,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="25.0">25</number>
.xi. 
<number box="[1307,1368,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</date>
, H.B. Leech (
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34700" box="[235,295,332,356]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">CAS</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,367,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Recognition</emphasis>
. Mid-sized species with 
<number box="[634,648,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of vertical bristles; antenna with scape and pedicel yellowish, postpedicel black, about 
<number box="[433,468,404,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as wide; thorax almost entirely finely greyish pollinose, katepisternum with large shining spot, acrostichals arranged in 
<number box="[702,716,439,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
irregular rows; legs almost entirely yellow, only last tarsomere darkened, mid tibia without apical spur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Re-description</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[543,684,511,535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5499999999999998" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="1.5499999999999998" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.7 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<number box="[845,878,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.9">1.9</number>
–2.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1000,1060,512,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1079,1148,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1818,1841]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,687,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1361,682,1797]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Platypalpus arnaudi (Melander), male. 1. habitus, lateral view. 2. wing, dorsal view. 3. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 4. epandrium with cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 5. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282719/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Fig. 
<number box="[1135,1148,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head black in groundcolour. Frons broad, densely light grey pollinose, widened toward ocellar tubercle. Face narrow, concolorous with frons. Ocellar tubercle with 
<number box="[465,479,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
long brown to yellowish brown proclinate anterior and 
<number box="[1102,1116,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
short posterior bristles. Two pairs of long brown to yellowish brown verticals. Occiput finely greyish pollinose, with numerous thin yellow to pale setae of different lengths. Antenna with scape and pedicel yellow to brownish yellow, postpedicel and stylus black; postpedicel conical, about 
<number box="[544,578,692,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X as long as wide; stylus as long as or slightly longer than postpedicel. Proboscis short, brownish yellow. Palpus small, yellow, pale pubescent, with several short pale setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Thorax brown in ground-colour, almost entirely finely greyish pollinose, sternopleuron with large shining spot; with pale to yellow setation. Postpronotal lobe with 
<number box="[761,775,799,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.0">1</number>
long inclinate bristle. Mesonotum with 
<number box="[1242,1256,799,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
notopleurals, 
<number box="[1422,1436,799,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.0">1</number>
postalar and 
<number box="[294,308,836,860]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
scutellar bristles (apical pair very long and cruciate, lateral pair very short); additionally, notopleural depression with several minute setulae and similar setulae present behind postpronotal lobe and on postsutural supra-alar space; dorsocentrals arranged in 
<number box="[644,658,908,932]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
irregular rows, lateroclinate, short, 
<number box="[1066,1080,908,932]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
prescutellars long; acrostichals arranged in 
<number box="[284,298,943,967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
irregular rows, short, lateroclinate anteriorly, lacking on prescutellar depression.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Legs almost entirely yellow, only last tarsomere darkened; mostly with pale to yellow setation. Fore femur and tibia slightly thickened, covered with short setae. Mid femur as wide as fore femur; with double row of mostly black ventral spinules; no posteroventral bristles. Mid tibia without apical spur, with spinules ventrally. 
<collectingCountry box="[1307,1363,1052,1076]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur with short anteroventral setae. 
<collectingCountry box="[495,551,1087,1111]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia unmodified, covered with short setae. Tarsi of all legs unmodified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[277,346,1124,1148]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1818,1841]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,687,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1361,682,1797]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Platypalpus arnaudi (Melander), male. 1. habitus, lateral view. 2. wing, dorsal view. 3. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 4. epandrium with cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 5. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282719/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Fig. 
<number box="[331,346,1124,1148]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) hyaline, with brownish yellow veins. One short costal bristle. Veins R 
<number box="[1163,1171,1139,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1180,1187,1139,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[1270,1276,1139,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1285,1294,1139,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
straight and parallel near wing margin; CuA 
<number box="[521,529,1178,1192]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
oblique; cells br and bm of subequal length but bm broader than br. Squama yellow, with pale setae. Halter pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Abdomen brown in ground-colour, finely greyish pollinose, covered with short pale setae. Terminalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1818,1841]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,687,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1361,682,1797]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Platypalpus arnaudi (Melander), male. 1. habitus, lateral view. 2. wing, dorsal view. 3. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 4. epandrium with cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 5. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282719/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,193,1273,1297]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
</figureCitation>
) rather large, concolorous with abdomen; left cercus digitiform, gradually narrowing, longer than right cercus, covered with unmodified setae; right cercus digitiform, covered with unmodified setae; left epandrial lamella subrectangular, with short narrow projection apically, with short to moderately long setae ventrally; right epandrial lamella rather elongate oval, with moderately long setae ventrally; right surstylus small, subtriangular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1418,1442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Female</emphasis>
. Similar to male. Abdominal segments 
<number box="[773,815,1417,1441]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
retracted and only partly visible; segment 
<number box="[1343,1357,1417,1441]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="8.0">8</number>
finely pollinose; cercus elongate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,562,1489,1514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" box="[199,562,1489,1514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1489,1514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,415,1489,1513]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">USA</collectingCountry>
(California).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1526,1550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Melander" box="[321,509,1525,1549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refString="Melander, A. L. (1960) A new species of Charadrodromia from California (Diptera: Empididae). The Wasmann Journal of Biology, 18, 129 - 130." type="journal article" year="1960">
Melander (
<number box="[443,501,1525,1549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1960.0">1960</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on numerous specimens taken from “Corte de Madera Creek, near Portola, California, San Mateo County”. 
<taxonomicName box="[753,984,1561,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arnaudi">
<emphasis box="[753,984,1561,1585]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Platypalpus arnaudi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily distinguished from other Nearctic species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[412,548,1598,1622]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hackmani">
<emphasis box="[412,548,1598,1622]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">P. hackmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by a large shining spot on the katepisternum and long postpedicel.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
